If no subcommand, displays the buoy state, any action engaged, and its
parameters.
    -sn: show the buoy serial number.
    -store: store the buoy parameters into the flash memory (with PT probe
            parameters too)
    -bypass: show or set the bypass opening time (in ms), if a third
             is given, it is the initial bypass time (in ms).
    -valve: show or set the valve opening time (in ms), and its flow
            coefficient.
    -pump: show or set the pump running time (in ms). If three arguments
           (subcmd + 2 numeric arguments), the time (in ms) and the
           PWM (in %). If four arguments is the pump flow coefficient and
           the fifth argument is the PWM to use to fill the bladder.
    -rate: the immobility threshold, when the buoy speed (in mbar/s, more or
           less same as cm/s), is less or equal to this value, buoy is in
           "park" state. When buoy speed is greater, "descent" state
           when > 0, "ascent" state otherwise.
    -surface: show or set the pressure (in mbar) of the surface.
    -dead: time to wait when the buoy has nothing TODO.
    -default: reset all parameters to their default values.
    -coeff: the magic coefficient that transforms the squarred buoy speed
            (in mbar/s) into oil volume to transfer (in mL or cm3). If two
            numeric args, they are the numerator and denominator.
    -stab: buoy tries to stabilize itself when the stage pressure reference
           is reached more or less its tolerance (if 1), or do nothing (0).
    -near: the distance to the stage pressure reference (in mbar) below
           which the buoy tries to not exceed the "near" speed parameter.
           If a 2nd numeric parameter is following, this is the maximum
           speed in mbar/s.
    -far: the distance to the stage pressure reference (in mbar) over which
          the buoy tries to go fastest than the "far" speed parameter.
           If a 2nd numeric parameter is following, this is the minimum
           speed in mbar/s.
    -delay: the time to wait on surface before to restart mission.
    -mmtime: the minimum mission time before accepting a MERMAID ascent
             request.

if no argument, show the last available pressure and temperature measures.
When one of the following parameter is changed, use "buoy store" to store
the change into the flash memory.
    -addr: show or set the P2T probe address necessary to scan it.
    -period: show or set the P2T scan period (in ms)
    -length: show or set the pressure historic depth, in number of
             measures.
    -dp: log P2T when previous pressure measures is different of the current
         one by "dp" mbar
    -dt: log P2T when previous temperature measures is different of the
         current one by "dt" m°Celsius
    -offset: show or set the pressure offset in mbar
reboot the buoy, if a third argument is given, it is the reboot code to use,\r\nuse code 0 to test the watchdog security.\r\n

when no argument, show all the stages informations. If one to four
arguments as follow "Pmbar (dPmbar) Ts (Xs)" where "Pmbar" is the stage
pressure reference (in mbar, mandatory), "dPmbar" is the tolerance
(in mbar, optional), "Ts" is the stage duration (in s, mandatory), "Xs"
it expiration date (in s, optional). Then the stage is added at the
end of the mission.
Otherwise, the 1st argument can be one of the following:
    -del: delete all the stages from the mission.
    -load: load the mission from the flash memory.
    -store: store mission into the flash memory.
    -max [P [T] [(t)]]: to set the maximum depth and/or mission duration.
